{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line a slice tin (15 x 25 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Place Crunchie Bars® into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, until evenly chopped. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place sugar, cocoa and egg into mixing bowl and blend <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then repeat blending <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Add cream or sweetened condensed milk and beat <nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add reserved Crunchie Bar® mixture and combine <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 3<\/nobr>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk.<\/strong> ","Place a layer of malt biscuits into prepared tin and cover with cream mixture. Place another layer of malt biscuits over the top (ensuring the biscuits are facing the same way), placing directly above the biscuits of the previous layer. This will form a giant ice cream sandwich that will be easier to serve.","Place in freezer until set (approx. 4 hours). When you are ready to serve, remove from the freezer and leave for 5 minutes before cutting around the malt biscuits into slices and serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 - 200 g Crunchie Bars® (approx. 2), broken into pieces","100 g raw sugar","30 g cocoa powder","1 egg","600 g pouring (whipping) cream or sweetened condensed milk","250 g malt biscuits (1 packet)"]}],"id":"r70970","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-Bep3kHUNKOI\/XZWe6-5kWtI\/AAAAAAAAe70\/NHaLb9bgp9gMPiLruZs4m1_aGvFZ5D6cQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_kLPoOu4Y3qXjXCPm.png","title":"Honeycomb ice cream slice","publishedAt":"2015-08-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"25 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"37 g","calories":"1595 kJ \/ 380 kcal"},"usefulItems":"slice tin (15 x 25 cm), baking paper, bowl, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["<strong>Choc mint ice cream slice<\/strong>: substitute Crunc